{
  "title": "ISic001096. M. Valerius Chorton honoured as euergetes",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] ΕΣ Λιλυβα[ῖται] <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν υἱὸν Χόρ\n                   τωνα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον\">[Μ(ᾶρκον)]</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">Οὐαλέριον</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του\">Δι[ογνή-]<br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[το]υ</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μηγαν\">Μηγαν</span></span>  <span data-text=\"υἱὸν\">υἱὸν</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">[Χόρ-]<br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>[τ]ωνα</span></span>  <span data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">εὐεργέταν</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΕΣΛΙΛΥΒΑ[....]<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν υἱὸν Χόρ\n                   τωνα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον\">[..]</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">ΟΥΑΛΕΡΙΟΝ</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του\">ΔΙ[....]<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[..]Υ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μηγαν\">ΜΗΓΑΝ</span></span><span data-text=\"υἱὸν\">ΥΙΟΝ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">[...]<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>[.]ΩΝΑ</span></span><span data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">ΕΥΕΡΓΕΤΑΝ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>text following Kaibel's interpretation of Gualtherus' transcription</span></span>; </li><li><span class=\"line 1\">line.1: <span>Gualtherus: ΙΡΕΣΔΙΛΙΟΑbOI</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"line 2\">line.2: <span>Gualtherus: ΟΥΑΛΕΡΙΟ ΟΝΔΙ</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"line 3\">line.3: <span>Gualtherus: ΥΛΗΡΑΝΥΙΟΝ</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"line 4\">line.4: <span>Gualtherus: ΩΝΑΕΧΕΡΣΕΤΑΝ</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The surviving manuscript tradition for this stone is extremely poor and confused. The transcription recorded by Tardia seems to conflate and repeat lines from the version of Gualtherus. The resolution proposed by Kaibel, of Gualtherus' text, as followed here, seems the least worst solution. A second, similar honorific for the same man is recorded in IG XIV.277 = CIL. X.7240 (<a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001097\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001097</a>, also lost and preserved in the antiquarian tradition). However, <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001660\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001660</a> = SEG 34.951 records honours for the father Diognetos Megas, providing some confirmation of the tradition, and confirming that Megas is a second name.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Gualtherus 1624 234 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388</a>  </li><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 128 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1769 cl.18, no.21 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1784 cl.18, no.21 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083</a>  </li><li> Franz 1853 5493 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a></li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">273</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a></li><li> Wilson 1990 317 n.15 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>Gualtherus records lunate epsilon</p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
